==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pseudopod
<hw>Pseu"do*pod</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pseudo-</ets> + <ets>-pod</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Any protoplasmic filament or irregular process
projecting from any unicellular organism, or from any animal or plant
call.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A rhizopod.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudopodial</ent>⟦br⟧
